[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] Since the trace depends only on the diagonal of the Jacobian $\partial _{z_{t}}f$ , this allows "free-form" Jacobian.
[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] Here, "free-form" means that there is no restriction on the Jacobian's form.
[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] It is contrasted with previous discrete models of normalizing flow, where the Jacobian is carefully designed to be only upper- or lower-diagonal, so that the Jacobian can be evaluated efficiently.
