[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] Indeed, CNF was first proposed in the same paper that proposed neural ODE.
[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] By adding extra dimensions, the CNF gains enough freedom to reverse orientation and go beyond ambient isotopy (just like how one can pick up a polygon from a desk and flip it around in 3-space, or unknot a knot in 4-space), yielding the "augmented neural ODE".
[src:flow-matching/flow-matching] Any homeomorphism of $\mathbb {R} ^{n}$ can be approximated by a neural ODE operating on $\mathbb {R} ^{2n+1}$ , proved by combining Whitney embedding theorem for manifolds and the universal approximation theorem for neural networks.
